southbound.description: This API enables the creation of product definitions and relationships between them. 6RS supports product relationships using a unit of measure hierarchy (e.g. Each → Pack → Case). Typically, a unit of measure has a identifier, quantity and a list of (scannable) UPC barcodes. For example, you may have individual red pens (EA), packs of 24 red pens (PK), cases of 144 red pens (CS) and/or cases of 6 packs of red pens (CS). By defining one or more units of measure you may then store, order and pick a subset of these units of measure.
This API specifies a group of pick tasks where each pick task minimally includes the product to pick, the location to pick from and the quantity to pick.
